article.headline: Army 62, Brown 54
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Jarrell Brown came off the bench to score 21 points and Army shot 93.8 percent from the free throw line to beat Brown University 62-54 Saturday. Army (4-2) is off to its best six-game start since the 1994-95 team also went 4-2. Brown, a junior guard who fills the role of Army's sixth man, scored 15 of his points in the first half, which ended with the Cadets leading 25-19. Army led 6-5 when Brown entered the game and scored 15 of the Cadets' next 19 points. Marcus Becker led the Bears (1-5) by scoring a career-high 21 points -- 14 in the second half as Brown rallied to tie the game three times, the last at 41-41 with 9:13 remaining. Army then went on a 6-0 run with Matt Bell burying a 3-point shot, Cory Sinning putting in a rebound and Bell adding a jumper from the left corner. Bell finished with 13 points, and Sinning had 10. The Cadets sealed the victory by converting 11 of their last 12 free throw shots. Army was 15-for-16 from the free throw line. Brown only led once in the game, when Becker scored off the opening tap to make it 2-0. Keenan Jeppesen contributed 12 points for the Bears, who shot 40.5 percent from the floor.
